(8, 1, 2, 'Ampharos', '[L][L][L] Gigaspark : 40\r\nFlip a coin. If heads, the Defending Pokémon is now Paralyzed and this attack does 10 damage to each of your opponent''s Benched Pokémon. (Don''t apply Weakness and Resistance for Benched Pokémon.)', NULL),
(8, 2, 2, 'Azumarill', '[C][C] Tackle : 20\r\n\r\n[W][W][W] Bubble Shower: 30\r\nFlip a coin. If heads, the Defending Pokémon is now Paralyzed and this attack does 10 damage to each of your opponent''s Benched Pokémon. (Don''t apply Weakness and Resistance for Benched Pokémon.)', NULL),
(8, 3, 2, 'Bellossom', '[G] Sweet Nectar :\r\nFlip a coin. If heads, remove all damage counters from 1 of your Pokémon.\r\n\r\n[G][G][C] Flower Dance : 30×\r\nDoes 30 damage times the number of cards with Bellossom in their name that you have in play (including this one).', NULL),
(8, 4, 2, 'Feraligatr', 'Pokémon Power : Berserk\r\nWhen you play Feraligatr from your hand, flip a coin. If heads, discard the top 5 cards of your opponent''s deck. If tails, discard the top 5 cards from your deck.\r\n\r\n[W][W][W][W] Chomp : 50+\r\nFlip a number of coins equal to the number of damage counters on Feraligatr. This attack does 50 damage plus 10 more damage for each heads.', 'Berserk'),
(8, 5, 2, 'Feraligatr', 'Pokémon Power : Downpour\r\nAs often as you like during your turn (before your attack), you may discard a [W] Energy card from your hand. This power can''t be used if Feraligatr is Asleep, Confused, or Paralyzed.\r\n\r\n[W][W][W] Riptide : 10+\r\nDoes 10 damage plus 10 damage times the number of [W] Energy cards in your discard pile. Then, shuffle all [W] Energy cards from your discard pile into your deck.', 'Riptide'),
(8, 6, 2, 'Heracross', 'Pokémon Power : Final Blow\r\nIf Heracross''s remaining HP are 20 of less, you may make its Megahorn attack''s base damage 120 instead of 60. This power can''t be used if Heracross is Asleep, Confused, or Paralyzed.\r\n\r\n[G][G][G] Megahorn : 60\r\nFlip a coin. If tails, this attack does nothing.', NULL),
(8, 7, 2, 'Jumpluff', '[G] Sleep Powder : 20\r\nThe Defending Pokémon is now Asleep.\r\n\r\n[G] Leech Seed : 20\r\nIf this attack damages the Defending Pokémon (after applying Weakness and Resistance), remove 1 damage counter from Jumpluff, if it has any.', NULL),
(8, 8, 2, 'Kingdra', '[W][W][C] Agility : 30\r\nFlip a coin. If heads, during your opponent''s next turn, prevent all effects of attacks, including damage, done to Kingdra.\r\n\r\n[W][W][W][W] Dragon Tornado : 50\r\nIf this attack doesn''t Knock Out the Defending Pokémon, and if there are any Pokémon on your opponent''s Bench, choose 1 of them and switch it with the Defending Pokémon.', 'Dragon Tornado'),
(8, 9, 2, 'Lugia', '[R][W][L] Elemental Blast : 90\r\nDiscard a [R] Energy card, a [W] Energy card, and a [L] Energy card attached to Lugia in order to use this attack.', 'Elemental Blast'),
(8, 10, 2, 'Meganium', 'Pokémon Power : Herbal Scent\r\nWhen you play Meganium from your hand, you may flip a coin. If heads, remove all damage counters from all [G] Pokémon in play.\r\n\r\n[G][G][C][C] Body Slam : 40\r\nFlip a coin. If heads, the Defending Pokémon is now Paralyzed.', NULL),
(8, 11, 2, 'Meganium', 'Pokémon Power : Wild Growth\r\nAs long as Meganium is in play each [G] Energy card attached to your [G] Pokémon instead provides [G][G]. This power stops working while Meganium is Asleep, Confused, or Paralyzed.\r\n\r\n[G][G][G][G] Soothing Scent : 40\r\nThe Defending Pokémon is now Asleep.', 'Wild Growth'),
(8, 12, 2, 'Pichu', 'If this Baby Pokémon is your Active Pokémon and your opponent tries to attack, your opponent flips a coin (before doing anything required in order to use that attack). If tails, your opponent''s turn ends without an attack.\r\n\r\n[C] Zzzap :\r\nDoes 20 damage to each Pokémon in play that has a Pokémon Power. Don''t apply Weakness and Resistance.', 'Zzzap'),
(8, 13, 2, 'Skarmory', '[C] Claw : 20\r\nFlip a coin. If tails, this attack does nothing.\r\n\r\n[M][C][C] Steel Wing : 30\r\nFlip a coin. If heads, all damage done by attacks to Skarmory during your opponent''s next turn is reduced by 20 (after applying Weakness and Resistance).', NULL),
(8, 14, 2, 'Slowking', 'Pokémon Power : Mind Games\r\nWhenever your opponent plays a Trainer card, you may flip a coin. If heads, that card does nothing. Put it on top of your opponent''s deck. This power can''t be used if Slowking is Asleep, Confused, or Paralyzed.\r\n\r\n[P][P][P] Mind Blast : 20+\r\nFlip a coin. If heads, this attack does 20 damage plus 10 more damage and the Defending Pokémon is now Confused. If tails, this attack does 20 damage.', 'Mind Games'),
(8, 15, 2, 'Steelix', '[C][C] Tackle : 20\r\n\r\n[M][C][C] Tail Crush : 30+\r\nFlip a coin. If heads, this attack does 30 damage plus 20 more damage; if tails, this attack does 30 damage.', 'Tail Crush'),
(8, 16, 2, 'Togetic', '[C] Super Metronome :\r\nFlip a coin. If heads, choose an attack on 1 of your opponent''s Pokémon. Super Metronome copies that attack except for its Energy cost. (You must still do anything else in order to use that attack.) (No matter what type the Defending Pokémon is, Togetic''s type is still [C].) Togetic performs that attack. (Togetic can make that attack even if it does not have the appropriate number or type of Energy attached to it necessary to make the attack.)\r\n\r\n[C][C][C] Fly : 30\r\nFlip a coin. If heads, during your opponent''s next turn, prevent all effects of attacks, including damage, done to Togetic; if tails, this attack does nothing (not even damage).', 'Super Metronome'),
(8, 17, 2, 'Typhlosion', 'Pokémon Power : Fire Recharge\r\nOnce during your turn (before your attack), you may flip a coin. If heads, attach a [R] Energy card from your discard pile to 1 of your [R] Pokémon. This power can''t be used if Typhlosion is Asleep, Confused, or Paralyzed.\r\n\r\n[R][R][R][R] Flame Burst : 60+\r\nFlip a coin. If heads, this attack does 60 damage plus 20 more damage and does 20 damage to Typhlosion. If tails, this attack does 60 damage.', 'Fire Recharge'),
(8, 18, 2, 'Typhlosion', 'Pokémon Power : Fire Boost\r\nWhen you play Typhlosion from your hand, you may flip a coin. If heads, search your deck for up to 4 [R] Energy cards and attach them to Typhlosion. Shuffle your deck afterward.\r\n\r\n[R][R][R][R] Flame Wheel : 80\r\nDiscard 3 [R] Energy cards attached to Typhlosion in order to use this attack. Do 20 damage to each Benched Pokémon (yours and your opponent''s). (Don''t apply Weakness and Resistance for Benched Pokémon.)', 'Fire Boost'),
(8, 19, 2, 'Metal Energy', 'Damage done to the Pokémon Metal Energy is attached to is reduced by 10 (after applying Weakness and Resistance). If the Pokémon Metal Energy is attached to isn''t [M], whenever it damages a Pokémon, reduce that damage by 10 (before applying Weakness and Resistance).\r\n\r\nMetal Energy provides [M] Energy. (Doesn''t count as a basic Energy card.)', NULL),
(8, 20, 2, 'Cleffa', 'If this Baby Pokémon is your Active Pokémon and your opponent tries to attack, your opponent flips a coin (before doing anything required in order to use that attack). If tails, your opponent''s turn ends without an attack.\r\n\r\n[C] Eeeeeeek :\r\nShuffle your hand into your deck, then draw 7 cards.', 'Eeeeeeek'),
(8, 21, 2, 'Donphan', '[F] Flail : 10×\r\nDoes 10 damage times the number of damage counters on Donphan.\r\n\r\n[F][F][F] Rapid Spin : 50\r\nIf your opponent has any Benched Pokémon, he or she chooses 1 of them and switches it with his or her Active Pokémon, then, if you have any Benched Pokémon, you switch 1 of them with your Active Pokémon. (Do the damage before switching the Pokémon.)', 'Rapid Spin'),
(8, 22, 2, 'Elekid', 'If this Baby Pokémon is your Active Pokémon and your opponent tries to attack, your opponent flips a coin (before doing anything required in order to use that attack). If tails, your opponent''s turn ends without an attack.\r\n\r\nPokémon Power : Playful Punch\r\nOnce during your turn (before your attack), your may flip a coin. If heads, do 20 damage to your opponent''s Active Pokémon. (Apply Weakness and Resistance.) Either way, this ends your turn. This power can''t be used if Elekid is Asleep, Confused, or Paralyzed.', 'Playful Punch'),
(8, 23, 2, 'Magby', 'If this Baby Pokémon is your Active Pokémon and your opponent tries to attack, your opponent flips a coin (before doing anything required in order to use that attack). If tails, your opponent''s turn ends without an attack.\r\n\r\n[C] Sputter : 10\r\nAll Pokémon Powers stop working until the end of your next turn.', 'Sputter'),
(8, 24, 2, 'Murkrow', '[D] Mean Look :\r\nThe Defending Pokémon can''t retreat as long as Murkrow remains your Active Pokémon. (Benched or evolving either Pokémon ends this effect.)\r\n\r\n[D][C] Feint Attack :\r\nChoose 1 of your opponent''s Pokémon. This attack does 20 damage to that Pokémon. This attack''s damage isn''t affected by Weakness, Resistance, Pokémon Powers, or any other effects on the Defending Pokémon.', 'Mean Look'),
(8, 25, 2, 'Sneasel', '[C] Fury Swipes : 10×\r\nFlip 3 coins. This attack does 10 damage times the number of heads.\r\n\r\n[D][D] Beat Up : 20×\r\nFlip a coin for each of your Pokémon in play (including this one). This attack does 20 damage times the number of heads.', 'Beat Up'),
(8, 26, 2, 'Aipom', '[C] Pilfer :\r\nShuffle Aipom and all cards attached to it into your deck. Flip a coin. If heads, shuffle a card from your discard pile into your deck.\r\n\r\n[C] Tail Rap : 10×\r\nFlip 2 coins. This attack does 10 damage times the number of heads.', 'Pilfer'),
(8, 27, 2, 'Ariados', '[G] Spider Web :\r\nFlip a coin. If heads, the Defending Pokémon can''t retreat. (Benching or evolving that Pokémon ends this effect.)\r\n\r\n[G][G][G] Poison Bite : 20\r\nIf this attack damages the Defending Pokémon, the Defending Pokémon is now Poisoned and you remove a number of damage counters from Ariados equal to half that damage (rounded up to the nearest 10). If Ariados has fewer damage counters than that remove all of them.', 'Spider Web'),
(8, 28, 2, 'Bayleef', '[G][C] Poisonpowder : 20\r\nFlip a coin. If heads, the Defending Pokémon is now Poisoned.\r\n\r\n[G][G][C] Pollen Shield : 30\r\nDuring your opponent''s next turn, Bayleef can''t become Asleep, Confused, Paralyzed, or Poisoned. (All other effects of attacks, Pokémon Powers and Trainer cards still happen.)', 'Poisonpowder'),
(8, 29, 2, 'Bayleef', '[G] Sweet Scent :\r\nFlip a coin. If heads and if any of your Pokémon have any damage counters on them, then remove 2 damage counters from 1 of them (or 1 if it only has 1). If tails and if any of your opponent''s Pokémon have any damage counters on them, choose 1 of them and remove 2 damage counters from it (or 1 if it only has 1).\r\n\r\n[G][G][G] Double Razor Leaf : 40×\r\nFlip 2 coins. This attack does 40 damage times the number of heads.', 'Double Razor Leaf'),
(8, 30, 2, 'Clefairy', '[C][C] Doubleslap : 10×\r\nFlip 2 coins. This attack does 10 damage times the number of heads.\r\n\r\n[C][C][C] Squaredance :\r\nFlip a number of coins equal to the total number of Pokémon in play. For each heads, you may search your deck for a basic Energy card, show it to your opponent, and put it into your hand. Shuffle your deck afterward.', 'Squaredance'),
(8, 31, 2, 'Croconaw', '[C] Screech :\r\nUntil the end of your next turn, if an attack damages the Defending Pokémon (after applying Weakness and Resistance), that attack does 20 more damage to the Defending Pokémon.\r\n\r\n[W][W][C] Jaw Clamp : 30\r\nUntil the end of your opponent''s next turn, as long as Croconaw is your Active Pokémon, the Defending Pokémon can''t retreat, and if the effect of an attack, Pokémon Power, or Trainer card would change that player''s Active Pokémon, that part of the effect does nothing.', 'Jaw Clamp'),
(8, 32, 2, 'Croconaw', '[C][C] Tackle : 20\r\n\r\n[W][W][C] Sweep Away : 50\r\nDiscard the top 3 cards from your deck.', 'Sweep Away'),
(8, 33, 2, 'Electabuzz', '[C][C] Punch : 20\r\n\r\n[L][L][L] Swift : 30\r\nThis attack''s damage isn''t affected by Weakness, Resistance, Pokémon Powers, or any other effects on the Defending Pokémon.', 'Swift'),
(8, 34, 2, 'Flaaffy', '[L] Discharge : 30×\r\nDiscard all [L] Energy cards attached to Flaaffy in order to use this attack. Flip a number of coins equal to the number of [L] Energy cards you discarded. This attack does 30 damage times then number of heads.\r\n\r\n[L][L] Electric Current : 20\r\nTake 1 [L] Energy cards attached to Flaaffy and attach it to 1 of your Benched Pokémon. If you have no Benched Pokémon, discard that Energy card.', 'Discharge'),
(8, 35, 2, 'Furret', '[C][C] Quick Attack : 20+\r\nFlip a coin. If heads, this attack does 20 damage plus 10 more damage; if tails, this attack does 20 damage.\r\n\r\n[C][C][C] Slam : 30×\r\nFlip 2 coins. This attack does 30 damage times the number of heads.', NULL),
(8, 36, 2, 'Gloom', '[G][C] Strange Powder : 20\r\nFlip a coin. If heads, the Defending Pokémon is now Confused. If tails, the Defending Pokémon is now Asleep.\r\n\r\n[G][G][C] Sticky Nectar : 20+\r\nFlip a coin. If heads, this attack does 20 damage plus 10 more damage and, until the end of your next turn, as long as Gloom is your Active Pokémon, the Defending Pokémon can''t retreat, and if the effect of an attack, Pokémon Power, or Trainer card would change that player''s Active Pokémon, that part of the effect does nothing. If tails, this attack does 20 damage.', 'Strange Powder'),
(8, 37, 2, 'Granbull', '[C][C] Tackle : 20\r\n\r\n[C][C][C] Raging Charge : 10+\r\nThis attack does 10 damage plus 10 more damage for each damage counter on Granbull. Then, Granbull does 20 damage to itself.', NULL),
(8, 38, 2, 'Lanturn', 'Pokémon Power : Hydroelectric Power\r\nYou may make Floodlight do 10 more damage for each [W] Energy attached to Lanturn, but not used to pay for Floodlight''s Energy cost. This power can''t be used if Lanturn is Asleep, Confused, or Paralyzed.\r\n\r\n[L][L] Floodlight : 20\r\nFlip a coin. If heads, the Defending Pokémon is now Paralyzed.', 'Hydroelectric Power'),
(8, 39, 2, 'Ledian', '[G][G] Baton Pass : 30\r\nIf you have any [G] Pokémon on your Bench, remove all [G] Energy cards from Ledian and attach them to 1 of those Pokémon, then switch Ledian with that Pokémon.', 'Baton Pass'),
(8, 40, 2, 'Magmar', '[C][C] Tail Slap : 20\r\n\r\n[R][R][C] Magma Punch : 40', NULL),
(8, 41, 2, 'Miltank', '[C] Milk Drink :\r\nFlip 2 coins. Remove 2 damage counters times the number of heads from Miltank. If it has fewer damage counters than that, remove all of them.\r\n\r\n[C][C][C] Body Slam : 20\r\nFlip a coin. If heads, the Defending Pokémon is now Paralyzed.', NULL),
(8, 42, 2, 'Noctowl', 'Pokémon Power : Glaring Gaze\r\nOnce during your turn (before your attack), you may flip a coin. If heads, look at your opponent''s hand. If your opponent has any Trainer cards there, choose 1 of them. Your opponent shuffles that card into his or her deck. This power can''t be used if Noctowl is Asleep, Confused, or Paralyzed.\r\n\r\n[C][C][C] Wing Attack : 30', 'Glaring Gaze'),
(8, 43, 2, 'Phanpy', '[C] Tackle : 10\r\n\r\n[F] Endure :\r\nFlip a coin. If heads, then if, during your opponent''s next turn, Phanpy would be Knocked Out by an attack, Phanpy isn''t Knocked Out and its remaining HP become 10 instead.', NULL),
(8, 44, 2, 'Piloswine', '[W][W] Freeze : 10\r\nFlip a coin. If heads, the Defending Pokémon can''t attack. (Benching or evolving the Defending Pokémon ends this effect.)\r\n\r\n[W][W][W] Blizzard : 30\r\nFlip a coin. If heads, this attack does 10 damage to each of your opponent''s Benched Pokémon; if tails, this attack does 10 damage to each of your own Benched Pokémon. (Don''t apply Weakness and Resistance for Benched Pokémon.)', NULL),
(8, 45, 2, 'Quagsire', '[W][W] Surf : 30\r\n\r\n[F][F][C][C] Earthquake : 60\r\nDoes 10 damage to each of your own Benched Pokémon. (Don''t apply Weakness and Resistance for Benched Pokémon.)', NULL),
(8, 46, 2, 'Quilava', '[R][C] Ember : 30\r\nDiscard 1 [R] Energy card attached to Quilava in order to use this attack.\r\n\r\n[R][R] Fire Wind : 20\r\nIf your opponent has any Benched Pokémon, choose 1 of them. Flip 2 coins. For each heads, this attack does 10 damage to that Pokémon. (Don''t apply Weakness and Resistance.)', 'Fire Wind'),
(8, 47, 2, 'Quilava', '[R][R] Smokescreen : 20\r\nIf the Defending Pokémon tries to attack during your opponent''s next turn, your opponent flips a coin. If tails, that attack does nothing.\r\n\r\n[R][R][R] Char : 30\r\nIf the Defending Pokémon doesn''t have a Char counter on it, flip a coin. If heads, put a Char counter on it. A Char counter requires your opponent to flip a coin after every turn. If tails, put 2 damage counters on the Pokémon with that Char counter. (Char counters stay on the Pokémon as long as it''s in play.)', 'Char'),
(8, 48, 2, 'Seadra', '[W] Bubble : 10\r\nFlip a coin. If heads, the Defending Pokémon is now Paralyzed.\r\n\r\n[W][W] Mud Splash : 30\r\nIf your opponent has any Benched Pokémon, choose of them and flip a coin. If heads, this attack does 10 damage to that Pokémon. (Don''t apply Weakness and Resistance for Benched Pokémon.)', 'Mud Splash'),
(8, 49, 2, 'Skiploom', '[G] Poisonpowder : 10\r\nThe Defending Pokémon is now Poisoned.\r\n\r\n[G] Stun Spore : 10\r\nFlip a coin. If heads, the Defending Pokémon is now Paralyzed.', NULL),
(8, 50, 2, 'Sunflora', '[G][G][G] Petal Dance : 30×\r\nFlip 3 coins. This attack does 30 damage times the number of heads. Sunflora is now Confused (after doing damage).', NULL),
(8, 51, 2, 'Togepi', '[C][C] Poison Barb : 10\r\nThe Defending Pokémon is now Poisoned.', 'Poison Barb'),
(8, 52, 2, 'Xatu', '[P] Prophecy :\r\nLook at the top 3 cards of either player''s deck and rearrange them as you like.\r\n\r\n[P][P][P] Confuse Ray : 30\r\nFlip a coin. If heads, the Defending Pokémon is now Confused.', NULL),
(8, 53, 2, 'Chikorita', '[C] Tackle : 10\r\n\r\n[G] Deflector :\r\nDuring your opponent''s next turn, whenever Chikorita takes damage, divide that damage in half (rounded down to the nearest 10). (Any other effects still happen.)', 'Deflector'),
(8, 54, 2, 'Chikorita', '[C] Growl :\r\nIf the Defending Pokémon attacks Chikorita during your opponent''s next turn, any damage done to Chikorita is reduced by 10 (before applying Weakness and Resistance). (Benched or evolving either Pokémon ends this effect.)\r\n\r\n[G][C] Razor Leaf : 20', 'Growl'),
(8, 55, 2, 'Chinchou', '[L] Supersonic :\r\nFlip a coin. If heads, the Defending Pokémon is now Confused.\r\n\r\n[W] Flail : 10×\r\nDoes 10 damage times the number of damage counters on Chinchou.', 'Flail'),
(8, 56, 2, 'Cyndaquil', '[C] Leer :\r\nFlip a coin. If heads, the Defending Pokémon can''t attack Cyndaquil during your opponent''s next turn. (Benching or evolving either Pokémon ends this effect.)\r\n\r\n[R][C] Swift : 20\r\nThis attack''s damage isn''t affected by Weakness, Resistance, Pokémon Powers, or any other effects on the Defending Pokémon.', 'Swift'),
(8, 57, 2, 'Cyndaquil', '[R] Fireworks : 20\r\nFlip a coin. If tails, discard 1 Energy card attached to Cyndaquil.\r\n\r\n[C][C] Quick Attack : 10+\r\nFlip a coin. If heads, this attack does 10 damage plus 20 more damage; if tails, this attack does 10 damage.', 'Fireworks'),
(8, 58, 2, 'Girafarig', '[C][C] Agility : 10\r\nFlip a coin. If heads, during your opponent''s next turn, prevent all effects of attacks, including damage, done to Girafarig.\r\n\r\n[P][P] Psybeam : 20\r\nFlip a coin. If heads, the Defending Pokémon is now Confused.', NULL),
(8, 59, 2, 'Gligar', '[F] Poison Sting : 10\r\nFlip a coin. If heads, the Defending Pokémon is now Poisoned.\r\n\r\n[C][C] Slash : 20', 'Poison Sting'),
(8, 60, 2, 'Hoothoot', '[C] Hypnosis :\r\nThe Defending Pokémon is now Asleep.\r\n\r\n[C][C] Peck : 20', NULL),
(8, 61, 2, 'Hoppip', '[C] Hop : 10\r\n\r\n[G] Sprout :\r\nSearch your deck for a Basic Pokémon named Hoppip and put it onto your Bench. Shuffle your deck afterward. (You can''t use this attack if your Bench is full.)', 'Sprout'),
(8, 62, 2, 'Horsea', '[W][W] Fin Slap : 20+\r\nIf an attack damaged Horsea during your opponent''s last turn, this attack does 20 damage plus 10 more damage. If not, this attack does 20 damage.', 'Fin Slap'),
(8, 63, 2, 'Ledyba', '[G] Supersonic :\r\nFlip a coin. If heads, the Defending Pokémon is now Confused.\r\n\r\n[G][G] Comet Punch : 10×\r\nFlip 4 coins. This attack does 10 damage times the number of heads.', NULL),
(8, 64, 2, 'Mantine', '[W][W] Undulate : 20\r\nFlip a coin. If heads, during your opponent''s next turn, prevent all effects of attacks, including damage, done to Mantine.', 'Undulate'),
(8, 65, 2, 'Mareep', '[L] Static Electricity :\r\nFor each Mareep in play, you may search your deck for a [L] Energy cards and attach it to Mareep. Shuffle your deck afterward.\r\n\r\n[L][L] Thundershock : 20\r\nFlip a coin, if heads, the Defending Pokémon is now Paralyzed.', 'Static Electricity'),
(8, 66, 2, 'Marill', '[C] Defense Curl :\r\nFlip a coin. If heads, prevent all damage done to Marill during your opponent''s next turn. (Any other effects of attacks still happen.)\r\n\r\n[W][W] Bubble Bomb : 30\r\nFlip a coin. If heads, the Defending Pokémon is now Paralyzed. If tails, Marill does 10 damage to itself.', 'Bubble Bomb');
INSERT INTO `cards_names` (`set_id`, `number`, `local_language_id`, `name`, `text`, `description`) VALUES
(8, 67, 2, 'Natu', '[C] Peck : 10\r\n\r\n[P][P] Telekinesis :\r\nChoose 1 of your opponent''s Pokémon. This attack does 20 damage to that Pokémon. Don''t apply Weakness and Resistance for this attack. (Any other effects that would happen after applying Weakness and Resistance still happen.)', 'Telekinesis'),
(8, 68, 2, 'Oddish', '[C] Hide :\r\nFlip a coin. If heads, during your opponent''s next turn, prevent all effects of attacks, including damage, done to Oddish.\r\n\r\n[G][G] Absorb : 20\r\nRemove a number of damage counters from Oddish equal to half the damage done to the Defending Pokémon (after applying Weakness and Resistance) (rounded up to the nearest 10). If Oddish has fewer damage counters than that, remove all of them.', 'Hide'),
(8, 69, 2, 'Onix', '[C] Screech :\r\nUntil the end of your next turn, if an attack damages the Defending Pokémon (after applying Weakness and Resistance), that attack does 20 more damage to the Defending Pokémon.\r\n\r\n[F][F] Rage : 10+\r\nDoes 10 damage plus 10 more damage for each damage counter on Onix.', 'Rage'),
(8, 70, 2, 'Pikachu', '[C] Quick Attack : 10+\r\nFlip a coin. If heads, this attack does 10 damage plus 20 more damage; if tails, this attack does 10 damage.\r\n\r\n[L][L][C] Agility : 20\r\nFlip a coin. If heads, during your opponent''s next turn, prevent all effects of attacks, including damage, done to Pikachu.', NULL),
(8, 71, 2, 'Sentret', '[C] Fury Swipes : 10×\r\nFlip 3 coins. This attack does 10 damage times the number of heads.', NULL),
(8, 72, 2, 'Shuckle', '[G] Withdraw :\r\nFlip a coin. If heads, prevent all damage done to Shuckle during your opponent''s next turn. (Any other effects still happen.)\r\n\r\n[G][G] Wrap : 20\r\nFlip a coin. If heads, the Defending Pokémon is now Paralyzed.', NULL),
(8, 73, 2, 'Slowpoke', '[P] Psyshock : 10\r\nFlip a coin. If heads, the Defending Pokémon is now Paralyzed.\r\n\r\n[W] Water Gun : 10+\r\nDoes 10 damage plus 10 more damage for each [W] Energy attached to Slowpoke but not used to pay for this attack''s Energy cost. You can''t add more than 20 damage in this way.', 'Psyshock'),
(8, 74, 2, 'Snubbull', '[C] Roar :\r\nFlip a coin. If heads and if your opponent has any Benched Pokémon, he of she chooses 1 of them and switches it with the Defending Pokémon. (Do the damage before switching the Pokémon.)\r\n\r\n[C][C] Lick : 10\r\nFlip a coin. If heads, the Defending Pokémon is now Paralyzed.', NULL),
(8, 75, 2, 'Spinarak', '[C] Scary Face :\r\nFlip a coin. If heads, until the end of your opponent''s next turn, the Defending Pokémon can''t attack or retreat.\r\n\r\n[G] String Shot : 10\r\nFlip a coin. If heads, the Defending Pokémon is now Paralyzed.', NULL),
(8, 76, 2, 'Stantler', '[C][C] Stomp : 20+\r\nFlip a coin. If heads, this attack does 20 damage plus 10 more damage; if tails, this attack does 20 damage.\r\n\r\n[C][C][C] Mystifying Horns : 20\r\nFlip a coin. If heads, the Defending Pokémon is now Confused.', NULL),
(8, 77, 2, 'Sudowoodo', '[F] Flail : 10×\r\nDoes 10 damage times the number of damage counters on Sudowoodo.\r\n\r\n[F][C] Rock Throw : 30', 'Flail'),
(8, 78, 2, 'Sunkern', '[G] Growth :\r\nFlip a coin. If heads, you may attach up to 2 [G] Energy cards from your hand to Sunkern.\r\n\r\n[G][G][G] Mega Drain : 30\r\nRemove a number of damage counters from Sunkern equal to half the damage done to the Defending Pokémon (after applying Weakness and Resistance) (rounded up to the nearest 10). If Sunkern has fewer damage counters than that, remove all of them.', 'Growth'),
(8, 79, 2, 'Swinub', '[W] Powder Snow : 10\r\nThe Defending Pokémon is now Asleep.', 'Powder Snow'),
(8, 80, 2, 'Totodile', '[C] Bite : 10\r\n\r\n[W][C] Rage : 10+\r\nDoes 10 damage plus 10 more damage for each damage counter on Totodile.', 'Rage'),
(8, 81, 2, 'Totodile', '[C] Leer :\r\nFlip a coin. If heads, the Defending Pokémon can''t attack Totodile during your opponent''s next turn. (Benching or evolving either Pokémon ends this effect.)\r\n\r\n[W] Fury Swipes : 10×\r\nFlip 3 coins. This attack does 10 damage times the number of heads.', 'Fury Swipes'),
(8, 82, 2, 'Wooper', '[W] Amnesia :\r\nChoose 1 of the Defending Pokémon''s attacks. That Pokémon can''t use that attack during your opponent''s next turn.\r\n\r\n[C][C] Slam : 20×\r\nFlip 2 coins. This attack does 20 damage times the number of heads.', 'Amnesia'),
(8, 83, 2, 'Arcade Game', 'Shuffle you deck, then reveal the top 3 cards of it. If at least 2 of those cards share the same name, put all the ones with that name into your hand and shuffle the rest into your deck. If none of them do, shuffle all 3 into your deck.', NULL),
(8, 84, 2, 'Ecogym', 'Whenever an attack, Pokémon Power, or Trainer card discards another player''s non-[C] Energy card from a Pokémon, return that Energy card to its owner''s hand. (Energy cards that are discarded when that Pokémon is Knocked Out don''t count.)', NULL),
(8, 85, 2, 'Energy Charge', 'Flip a coin. If heads, shuffle up to 2 Energy cards from you discard pile into your deck.', NULL),
(8, 86, 2, 'Focus Band', 'Attach Focus Band to 1 of your Pokémon If the Pokémon that doesn''t have a Pokémon Tool attached to it.\r\n\r\nFocus Band is attached to would be Knocked Out by your opponent''s attack, flip a coin. If heads, that Pokémon is not Knocked Out and its remaining HP become 10 instead. Then, discard Focus Band.', NULL),
(8, 87, 2, 'Mary', 'Draw 2 cards. Then, shuffle 2 cards from your hand into your deck.', NULL),
(8, 88, 2, 'PokéGear', 'Look at the top 7 cards of your deck. If any of them are Trainer cards, you may show 1 of them to your opponent and put it into your hand. Shuffle your deck afterward. You can''t play any more Trainer cards this turn.', NULL),
(8, 89, 2, 'Super Energy Retrieval', 'Trade 2 of the other cards in your hand for 4 basic Energy cards from your discard pile. If you have fewer than 4 basic Energy cards there, take all of them.', NULL),
(8, 90, 2, 'Time Capsule', 'Your opponent may choose 5 Basic Pokémon, Evolution, and/or basic Energy cards in his or her discard pile. (If your opponent doesn''t have that many, he or she chooses all of them.) If your opponent chooses any cards, he or she shuffles them into his or her deck. Either way, you may do the same, and you can''t play any more Trainer cards this turn.', NULL),
(8, 91, 2, 'Bill''s Teleporter', 'Flip a coin. If heads, draw 4 cards.', NULL),
(8, 92, 2, 'Card-Flip Game', 'Choose 1 of your opponent''s face-down Prizes. Guess whether it is an Energy card, a Trainer card, or a Pokémon (Basic or Evolution) card. Flip the card face up (and leave it face up). If you guessed right, draw 2 cards.', NULL),
(8, 93, 2, 'Gold Berry', 'Attach Gold Berry to 1 of your Pokémon that doesn''t have a Pokémon Tool attached to it.\r\n\r\nAt any time between turns, if there are at least 4 damage counters of the Pokémon Gold Berry is attached to, you may remove 4 of them and discard Gold Berry. At the start of each turn, if there are at least 4 damage counters on the Pokémon Gold Berry is attached to, remove 4 of them and discard Gold Berry.', NULL),
(8, 94, 2, 'Miracle Berry', 'Attach Miracle Berry to 1 of your Pokémon that doesn''t have a Pokémon Tool attached to it.\r\n\r\nAt any time between turns, if the Pokémon Miracle Berry is attached to is Asleep, Confused, Paralyzed, or Poisoned, you may remove all those effects from that Pokémon and discard Miracle Berry. At the start of each turn, if the Pokémon Miracle Berry is attached to is Asleep, Confused, Paralyzed, or Poisoned, remove all of those effects from that Pokémon and discard Miracle Berry.', NULL),
(8, 95, 2, 'New Pokédex', 'Shuffle your deck. Then, look at up to 5 cards from the top of your deck and rearrange them as you like.', NULL),
(8, 96, 2, 'Professor Elm', 'Shuffle your hand into your deck. Then, draw 7 cards. You can''t play any more Trainer cards this turn.', NULL),
(8, 97, 2, 'Sprout Tower', 'All damage done by [C] Pokémon''s attacks is reduced by 30 (after applying Weakness and Resistance).', NULL),
(8, 98, 2, 'Super Scoop Up', 'Flip a coin. If heads, return 1 of your Pokémon and all cards attached to it to your hand.', NULL),
(8, 99, 2, 'Berry', 'At any time between turns, if there are at least 2 damage counters on the Pokémon Berry is attached to, you may remove 2 of them and discard Berry. At the start of each turn, if there are at least 2 damage counters on the Pokémon Berry is attached to, remove 2 of them and discard Berry.', NULL),
(8, 100, 2, 'Double Gust', 'If you have any Benched Pokémon, your opponent chooses 1 of them and switches it with your Active Pokémon. Then, if your opponent has any Benched Pokémon, choose 1 of them and switch it with his or her Active Pokémon.', NULL),
(8, 101, 2, 'Moo-Moo Milk', 'Choose 1 of your Pokémon. Flip 2 coins. Remove 2 damage counters times the number of heads from that Pokémon. If the Pokémon has fewer damage counters than that, remove all of them.', NULL),
(8, 102, 2, 'Pokémon March', 'Your opponent may search his or her deck for 1 Basic Pokémon card and put it onto his or her Bench. Then, you may search your deck for 1 Basic Pokémon card and put it onto your Bench. Then, each player shuffles his or her deck. (A player can''t do any of this if his or her Bench is full.)', NULL),
(8, 103, 2, 'Super Rod', 'Flip a coin. If heads, put an Evolution card from your discard pile, if any, into your hand. If tails, put a Basic Pokémon card from your discard pile, if any, into your hand.', NULL),
(8, 104, 2, 'Darkness Energy', 'If the Pokémon Darkness Energy is attached to damages the Defending Pokémon (after applying Weakness and Resistance), the attack does 10 more damage to the Defending Pokémon. At the end of every turn, put 1 damage counter on the Pokémon Darkness Energy is attached to, unless it''s [D] or has Dark in its name.\r\n\r\nDarkness Energy provides [D] Energy. (Doesn''t count as a basic Energy card.)', NULL),
(8, 105, 2, 'Recycle Energy', 'Recycle Energy provides [C] Energy. (Doesn''t count as a basic Energy card.)\r\nIf this card is put into your discard pile from play, return it to your hand.', NULL),
(8, 106, 2, 'Fighting Energy', '', NULL),
(8, 107, 2, 'Fire Energy', '', NULL),
(8, 108, 2, 'Grass Energy', '', NULL),
(8, 109, 2, 'Lightning Energy', '', NULL),
(8, 110, 2, 'Psychic Energy', '', NULL),
(8, 111, 2, 'Water Energy', '', NULL),
(9, 1, 2, 'Espeon', '[C][C] Bite : 20\r\n\r\n[P][P][C] Psychic : 30+\r\nDoes 30 damage plus 10 more damage for each Energy card attached to the Defending Pokémon.', NULL),
(9, 2, 2, 'Forretress', 'Pokémon Power : Spikes\r\nDuring your opponent''s turn, whenever 1 of your opponent''s Benched Pokémon becomes his or her Active Pokémon, Forretress does 10 damage to it. (Don''t apply Weakness and Resistance.) This power stops working if Forretress is Asleep, Confused, or Paralyzed.\r\n\r\n[M][C][C] Rapid Spin : 30\r\nIf your opponent has any Benched Pokémon, he or she chooses 1 of them and switches it with his or her Active Pokémon, then, if you have any Benched Pokémon, you switch 1 of them with your Active Pokémon. (Do the damage before switching the Pokémon.)', NULL),
(9, 3, 2, 'Hitmontop', '[F] Detect :\r\nFlip a coin. If heads, during your opponent''s next turn, prevent all effects of attacks, including damage, done to Hitmontop.\r\n\r\n[F][F][F] Triple Kick : 30×\r\nFlip 3 coins. This attack does 30 damage times the number of heads.', NULL),
(9, 4, 2, 'Houndoom', '[D][C][C] Crunch : 30\r\nUntil the end of your next turn, if an attack damages the Defending Pokémon (after applying Weakness and Resistance), that attack does 20 more damage to the Defending Pokémon.\r\n\r\n[R][R][C] Flamethrower : 50\r\nDiscard 1 [R] Energy card attached to Houndoom or this attack does nothing.', NULL),
(9, 5, 2, 'Houndour', '[R] Smog : 10\r\nFlip a coin. If heads, the Defending Pokémon is now Poisoned.\r\n\r\n[R][R] Collect Fire : 20\r\nIf there are any [R] Energy cards in your discard pile, choose 1 of them and attach it to Houndour.', NULL),
(9, 6, 2, 'Kabutops', '[C] Slash : 20\r\n\r\n[F] Hydrocutter : 40×\r\nFlip a number of coins equal to the number of Energy cards attached to Kabutops. This attack does 40 damage times the number of heads. You can''t flip more than 3 coins in this way.', NULL),
(9, 7, 2, 'Magnemite', '[C] Lock-on :\r\nDuring your next turn, treat any tails flipped when using Magnemite''s Electric Bolt attack as if they were heads. (Benching or evolving either Pokémon ends this effect.)\r\n\r\n[L][C] Electric Bolt : 50\r\nFlip 2 coins. If both are heads, the Defending Pokémon is now Paralyzed. If either of them is tails, this attack does nothing (not even damage).', NULL),
(9, 8, 2, 'Politoed', 'Pokémon Power: Frog Song\r\nWhenever Politoed''s attack damages the Defending Pokémon (after applying Weakness and Resistance), if there are more than 3 Poliwags, Poliwhirls, Poliwraths, and/or Politoeds in play (including your opponent''s), that attack does 40 more damage (no matter how many heads you get). This power stops working while Politoed is Asleep, Confused, or Paralyzed.\r\n\r\n[W][W][C][C] Doubleslap : 40×\r\nFlip 2 coins. This attack does 40 damage times the number of heads.', NULL),
(9, 9, 2, 'Poliwrath', '[F][C] Corkscrew Punch : 30\r\n\r\n[F][F][C][C] Submission: 70\r\nPoliwrath does 20 damage to itself.', NULL),
(9, 10, 2, 'Scizor', '[M] False Swipe : ?\r\nDoes damage equal to half the Defending Pokémon''s remaining HP (rounded down to the nearest 10).\r\n\r\n[C][C][C] Double Claw : 20+\r\nFlip 2 coins. This attack does 20 damage times the number of heads.', NULL),
(9, 11, 2, 'Smeargle', '[C][C] Sketch :\r\nIf the Defending Pokémon attacked last turn, and Smeargle was in play during that attack, Smeargle copies that attack except for its Energy costs and anything else required in order to use that attack.', NULL),
(9, 12, 2, 'Tyranitar', '[C][C][C] Slam : 30×\r\nFlip 2 coins. This attack does 30 damage times the number of heads.\r\n\r\n[D][D][C][C] Trample : 50\r\nFor each Benched Pokémon in play (yours and your opponent''s), flip a coin. If heads, this attack does 30 damage to that Pokémon. (Don''t apply Weakness and Resistance for Benched Pokémon.)', NULL),
(9, 13, 2, 'Umbreon', '[C][C] Bite : 20\r\n\r\n[D][D][C] Feint Attack :\r\nChoose 1 of your opponent''s Pokémon. This attack does 30 damage to that Pokémon. This attack''s damage isn''t affected by Weakness, Resistance, Pokémon Powers, or any other effects on the Defending Pokémon.', NULL),
(9, 14, 2, 'Unown A', 'You may have up to 4 Basic Pokémon cards in your deck with Unown in their names.\r\n\r\nPokémon Power : Anger\r\nWhenever 1 of your Pokémon with Unown in its name uses its Hidden Power attack, that attack does 10 more damage for each damage counter on Unown A. If you have more than 1 Unown A in play, use only 1 Anger for each attack.\r\n\r\n[P] Hidden Power : 10', NULL),
(9, 15, 2, 'Ursaring', '[C][C] Headpress : 20\r\nFlip a coin. If heads, the Defending Pokémon is now Paralyzed. If tails, this attack does nothing (not even damage).\r\n\r\n[C][C][C][C] Double Lariat : 40×\r\nFlip 2 coins. This attack does 40 damage times the number of heads.', NULL),
(9, 16, 2, 'Wobbuffet', '[P] Counter :\r\nIf an attack damages Wobbuffet during your opponent''s next turn (even if Wobbuffet is Knocked Out), flip a coin. If heads, Wobbuffet attacks the Defending Pokémon for an equal amount of damage.', NULL),
(9, 17, 2, 'Yanma', '[G] Shockwave :\r\nFlip a coin. If heads, this attack does 10 damage to each of your opponent''s Pokémon. Don''t apply Weakness and Resistance. Then, if your opponent has any Benched Pokémon, he or she chooses 1 of them and switches it with the Defending Pokémon.\r\n\r\n[G][G][G] Swift : 30\r\nThis attack''s damage isn''t affected by Weakness, Resistance, Pokémon Powers, or any other effects on the Defending Pokémon.', NULL),
(9, 18, 2, 'Beedrill', '[G] Triple Poison : 10\r\nFlip a coin. If heads, the Defending Pokémon is now Poisoned. Your opponent now puts 3 damage counters on it instead of 1 after each player''s turn (even if it was already Poisoned).\r\n\r\n[G][G][C] Pin Missile : 20×\r\nFlip 4 coins. This attack does 20 damage times the number of heads.', NULL),
(9, 19, 2, 'Butterfree', '[G][C] Magic Dust : 20\r\nFlip a coin. If heads, the Defending Pokémon is now either Asleep, Confused, Paralyzed, or Poisoned (your choice).\r\n\r\n[G][G][C] Hyper Reverse :\r\nDoes 10 damage times the number of Energy attached to the Defending Pokémon. After doing damage, remove a number of damage counters from Butterfree equal to the amount of damage done to the Defending Pokémon (after applying Weakness and Resistance).', NULL),
