(22, 84, 2, 'Pokémon Retriever', 'Search your discard pile for Basic Pokémon and Evolution cards. You may either show 1 Basic Pokémon or Evolution card to your opponent and put it into your hand, or show a combination of 3 Basic Pokémon or Evolution cards to your opponent and shuffle them into your deck.', NULL),
(22, 85, 2, 'Pow! Hand Extension', 'You may use this card only if you have more Prize cards left than your opponent.\r\n\r\nMove 1 Energy card attached to the Defending Pokémon to another of your opponent''s Pokémon. Or, switch 1 of your opponent''s Benched Pokémon with 1 of the Defending Pokémon. Your opponent chooses the Defending Pokémon to switch.', NULL),
(22, 86, 2, 'Rocket''s Admin.', 'You can play only one Supporter card each turn. When you play this card, put it next to your Active Pokémon. When your turn ends, discard this card.\r\n\r\nEach player shuffles his or her hand into his or her deck. Then, each player counts his or her Prize cards left and draws up to that many cards. (You draw your cards first.)', NULL),
(22, 87, 2, 'Rocket''s Hideout', 'This card stays in play when you play it. Discard this card if another Stadium card comes into play.\r\n\r\nEach Pokémon in play with Dark or Rocket''s in its name (both yours and your opponent''s) gets +20 HP.', NULL),
(22, 88, 2, 'Rocket''s Mission', 'You can play only one Supporter card each turn. When you play this card, put it next to your Active Pokémon. When your turn ends, discard this card.\r\n\r\nDiscard a card from your hand. Then, draw 3 cards. If you discarded a Pokémon that has Dark or Rocket''s in its name, draw 4 cards instead.', NULL),
(22, 89, 2, 'Rocket''s Poké Ball', 'Search your deck for a Pokémon that has Dark in its name, show it to your opponent, and put it into your hand. Shuffle your deck afterward.', NULL),
(22, 90, 2, 'Rocket''s Tricky Gym', 'This card stays in play when you play it. Discard this card if another Stadium card comes into play.\r\n\r\nEach Pokémon with Dark or Rocket''s in its name (both yours and your opponent''s) can use attacks on this card instead of its own.\r\n\r\n[C] Feint Attack: Does 20 damage to 1 of your opponent''s Pokémon. This attack''s damage isn''t affected by Weakness, Resistance, Poké-Powers, Poké-Bodies, or any other effects on that Pokémon.', NULL),
(22, 91, 2, 'Surprise! Time Machine', 'Choose 1 of your Evolved Pokémon, remove the highest Stage Evolution card from it, and shuffle it into your deck (this counts as devolving that Pokémon). If that Pokémon remains in play, search your deck for an Evolution card that evolves from that Pokémon and put it onto that Pokémon (this counts as evolving that Pokémon). Shuffle your deck afterward.', NULL),
(22, 92, 2, 'Swoop! Teleporter', 'Search your deck for a Basic Pokémon (excluding Pokémon-ex) and switch it with 1 of your Basic Pokémon (excluding Pokémon-ex) in play. (Any cards attached to that Pokémon, damage counters, Special Conditions, and effects on it are now on the new Pokémon.) Place the first Basic Pokémon in the discard pile. Shuffle your deck afterward.', NULL),
(22, 93, 2, 'Venture Bomb', 'Flip a coin. If heads, put 1 damage counter on 1 of your opponent''s Pokémon. If tails, put 1 damage counter on 1 of your Pokémon.', NULL),
(22, 94, 2, 'Dark Metal Energy', 'Attach Dark Metal Energy to 1 of your Pokémon. While in play, Dark Metal Energy provides [D] Energy and [M] Energy, but provides only 1 Energy at a time. (Doesn''t count as a basic Energy card when not in play and has no effect other than providing Energy.)', NULL),
(22, 95, 2, 'R Energy', 'R Energy can be attached only to a Pokémon that have Dark or Rocket''s in its name. While in play, R Energy provides 2 [D] Energy. (Doesn''t count as a basic Energy card.) If the Pokémon R Energy is attached to attacks, the attack does 10 more damage to the Active Pokémon (before applying Weakness and Resistance). When your turn ends, discard R Energy.', NULL),
