(22, 101, 2, 'Rocket''s Scizor ex', 'When Pokémon-ex has been Knocked Out, your opponent takes 2 Prize cards.\r\n\r\nPoké-Body : Dual Armor\r\nAs long as Rocket’s Scizor ex has any [M] Energy attached to it, Rocket’s Scizor ex is both [M] and [D] type.\r\n\r\n[C][C][C] Rotating Claws : 50\r\nYou may discard an Energy card attached to Rocket’s Scizor ex. If you do, search your discard pile for an Energy card (excluding the one you discarded) and attach it to Rocket’s Scizor ex.', NULL),
(22, 102, 2, 'Rocket''s Scyther ex', '', NULL),
(22, 103, 2, 'Rocket''s Sneasel ex', '', NULL),
(22, 104, 2, 'Rocket''s Snorlax ex', '', NULL),
(22, 105, 2, 'Rocket''s Suicune ex', 'When Pokémon-ex has been Knocked Out, your opponent takes 2 Prize cards.\r\n\r\nPoké-Body: Dark and Clear\r\nAs long as Rocket''s Suicune ex has any [D] Energy attached to it, Rocket''s Suicune ex can''t be affected by any Special Conditions.\r\n\r\n[C] Icy Wind : 10\r\nThe Defending Pokémon is now Asleep.\r\n\r\n[W][W][C] Hyper Splash : 50+\r\nIf the Defending Pokémon is a Stage 2 Evolved Pokémon, this attack does 50 damage plus 40 more damage.', NULL),
(22, 106, 2, 'Rocket''s Zapdos ex', 'When Pokémon-ex has been Knocked Out, your opponent takes 2 Prize cards.\r\n\r\nPoké-Body: Darkness Guard\r\nAs long as Rocket''s Zapdos ex has any [D] Energy attached to it, damage done to Rocket''s Zapdos ex by an opponent''s attack is reduced by 10 (after applying Weakness and Resistance).\r\n\r\n[C] Plasma : 10\r\nSearch your discard pile for a [L] Energy card and attach it to Rocket''s Zapdos ex.\r\n\r\n[L][L][C] Raging Thunder : 60\r\nThis attack does 30 damage to 1 of your Pokémon.', NULL),
(22, 107, 2, 'Mudkip Star', '[W] Whirlpool :\r\nFlip a coin. If heads, discard an Energy card attached to the Defending Pokémon.\r\n\r\n[W][W] Spring Back : 20+\r\nIf your opponent has only 1 Prize card left, this attack does 20 damage plus 50 more damage and the Defending Pokémon is now ', NULL),
(22, 108, 2, 'Torchic Star', '[R] Fireworks : 20\r\nFlip a coin. If tails, discard a [R] Energy card attached to Torchic.\r\n\r\n[R][R] Spring Back : 20+\r\nIf your opponent has only 1 Prize card left, this attack does 20 damage plus 50 more damage and the Defending Pokémon is now Confused.', NULL),
(22, 109, 2, 'Treecko Star', '[C] Tackle : 10\r\n\r\n[G][G] Spring Back : 20+\r\nIf your opponent has only 1 Prize card left, this attack does 20 damage plus 50 more damage and the Defending Pokémon is now Poisoned.', NULL),
(22, 110, 2, 'Charmeleon', '[R] Smokescreen : 10\r\nIf the Defending Pokémon tries to attack during your opponent''s next turn, your opponent flips a coin. If tails, that attack does nothing.\r\n\r\n[R][C] Fireworks : 40\r\nFlip a coin. If tails, discard a [R] Energy card attached to Charmeleon.', NULL),
(22, 111, 2, 'Here Comes Team Rocket!', 'You can play only one Supporter card each turn. When you play this card, put it next to your Active Pokémon. When your turn ends, discard this card.\r\n\r\nEach player plays with his or her Prize cards face up for the rest of the game.', NULL),
(23, 1, 2, 'Altaria', 'Poké-Body : Safeguard\r\nPrevent all effects of attacks, including damage, done to Altaria by your opponent''s Pokémon-ex.\r\n\r\n[L] Double Wing Attack :\r\nDoes 20 Damage to each Defending Pokémon.\r\n\r\n[W][C][C] Dive : 50', NULL),
(23, 2, 2, 'Beautifly', 'Poké-Body : Hunch\r\nAs long as Beautifly''s remaining HP is 40 or less, Beautifly does 40 more damage to the Defending Pokémon (before applying Weakness and Resistance).\r\n\r\n[G] Luring Antenna : 20\r\nBefore doing damage, you may choose 1 of your opponent''s Benched Pokémon and switch it with 1 of the Defending Pokémon. If you do, this attack does 20 damage to the new Defending Pokémon. Your opponent chooses the Defending Pokémon to switch.\r\n\r\n[G][C][C] Cutting Wind : 50', NULL),
(23, 3, 2, 'Breloom', '[C] Leaf Poison : 20\r\nIf Breloom has any [G] Energy attached to it, the Defending Pokémon is now Poisoned.\r\n\r\n[F][C][C] Hustle Punch : 70-\r\nDuring your next turn, Hustle Punch attack''s base damage is 50 instead of 70.', NULL),
(23, 4, 2, 'Camerupt', '[C] Back Burner :\r\nSearch your discard pile for up to 2 basic Energy cards and attach them to your Pokémon in any way you like.\r\n\r\n[R][C][C] Split Bomb :\r\nChoose 2 of your opponent''s Pokémon. This attack does 30 damage to each of them. (Don''t apply Weakness and Resistance for Benched Pokémon.)', NULL),
(23, 5, 2, 'Claydol', 'Poké-Power : Psychic Trance\r\nOnce during your turn (before you attack), if Claydol is your Active Pokémon, you may shuffle your hand into your deck. Then, draw a number of cards equal to the number of cards in your opponent''s hand. This power can''t be used if Claydol is affected by a Special Condition.\r\n\r\n[C][C] Ancient Mantra : 20+\r\nIf Claydol has any [P] Energy attached to it, the Defending Pokémon is now Confused. If Claydol has any [F] Energy attached to it, this attack does 20 damage plus 20 more damage.', NULL),
(23, 6, 2, 'Crawdaunt', 'Poké-Body : Dark Protection\r\nAny damage done to Crawdaunt by your opponent''s attacks is reduced by 10 for each [D] Energy attached to Crawdaunt (after applying Weakness and Resistance). You can''t reduce more than 20 damage in this way.\r\n\r\n[C][C] Bubblebeam : 20\r\nFlip a coin. If heads, the Defending Pokémon is now Paralyzed.\r\n\r\n[D][C][C] Cross-Cut : 40+\r\nIf the Defending Pokémon is an Evolved Pokémon, this attack does 40 damage plus 20 more damage.', NULL),
(23, 7, 2, 'Dusclops', '[P] Psychic Removal : 20\r\nFlip 2 coins. If both of them are heads, discard all Energy attached to the Defending Pokémon.\r\n\r\n[P][P][C] Powerful Hand :\r\nCount the number of cards in your hand. Put that many damage counters on the Defending Pokémon. You can''t put more than 7 damage counters in this way.', NULL),
(23, 8, 2, 'Gyarados', '[W] Dragon Spark :\r\nThis attack does 10 damage to each of your opponent''s Pokémon. (Don''t apply Weakness and Resistance for Benched Pokémon.)\r\n\r\n[C][C] Full Retaliation : 20×\r\nDoes 20 damage times the number of damage counters on all of your Magikarp.\r\n\r\n[W][W][C][C] Pulverize : 50+\r\nIf the Defending Pokémon already has at least 2 damage counters on it, this attack does 50 damage plus 50 more damage.', NULL),
(23, 9, 2, 'Jirachi', 'Poké-Power : Wishing Star\r\nOnce during your turn (before your attack), if Jirachi is your Active Pokémon, you may look at the top 5 cards of your deck, choose one of them, and put it into your hand. Shuffle your deck afterward. Jirachi and your other Active Pokémon, if any, are now Asleep. This power can''t be used if Jirachi is affected by a Special Condition.\r\n\r\n[M][C] Metallic Blow : 20+\r\nIf the Defending Pokémon has any Poké-Bodies, this attack does 20 damage plus 30 more damage.', NULL),
(23, 10, 2, 'Ludicolo', 'Poké-Power : Swing Dance\r\nOnce during your turn (before your attack), you may draw a card. This power can''t be used if Ludicolo is affected by a Special Condition.\r\n\r\n[W] Healing Steps : 30\r\nYou may discard as many cards as you like from your hand. If you do, remove that many damage counters from Ludicolo.\r\n\r\n[W][C][C] Circular Steps : 10×\r\nDoes 10 damage times the number of Pokémon in play (both yours and your opponent''s), excluding Ludicolo.', NULL),
(23, 11, 2, 'Metagross', 'Poké-Power : Super Connectivity\r\nOnce during your turn (before you attack), you may search your discard pile for a [P] or [M] Energy card and attach it to your Active Pokémon. Then, put 1 damage counter on that Pokémon. This power can''t be used if Metagross is affected by a Special Condition.\r\n\r\n[P][C] Link Blast : 70\r\nIf Metagross and the Defending Pokémon have a different amount of Energy attached to them, this attack''s base damage is 40 instead of 70.', NULL),
