(30, 1, 2, 'Ampharos δ', 'Poké-Body : Holon Veil\r\nTreat each Basic Pokémon and Evolution card in your deck, in your discard pile, in your hand, and in play as a Pokémon that has delta on its card.\r\n\r\n[C][C][C] Delta Circle : 20+\r\nDoes 20 damage plus 10 more damage for each Pokémon you have in play that has delta on its card.', NULL),
(30, 2, 2, 'Feraligatr δ', 'Poké-Body : Battle Aura\r\nEach of your Pokémon that has delta on its card does 10 more damage to the Defending Pokémon (before applying Weakness and Resistance).\r\n\r\n[C][C] Drag Off : 20\r\nBefore doing damage, you may choose 1 of your opponent’s Benched Pokémon and switch it with 1 of the Defending Pokémon. Your opponent chooses the Defending Pokémon to switch.\r\n\r\n[L][L][C] Sharp Fang : 60', NULL),
(30, 3, 2, 'Heracross δ', 'Poké-Body : Shining Horn\r\nAs long as Heracross is the only Pokémon you have in play, your opponent’s Basic Pokémon can’t attack.\r\n\r\n[C] Dig Deep :\r\nSearch you discard pile for an Energy card, show it to your opponent, and put it into your hand.\r\n\r\n[R][C] Extra Claws : 30+\r\nIf the Defending Pokémon is Pokémon-ex, this attack does 30 damage plus 20 more damage.', NULL),
(30, 4, 2, 'Meganium δ', 'Poké-Power : Evolutionary Call\r\nOnce during your turn, when you play Meganium from your hand to evolve 1 of your Pokémon. you may search your deck for up to 3 in any combination of Basic Pokémon or Evolution cards. Show them to your opponent and put them into your hand. Shuffle your deck afterward.\r\n\r\n[F][C] Delta Reduction : 40\r\nDuring your opponent’s next turn, any damage done by attacks from the Defending Pokémon is reduced by 30 (before applying Weakness and Resistance).\r\n\r\n[F][C][C] Mega Impact : 60', NULL),
(30, 5, 2, 'Milotic δ', 'Poké-Power : Sharing\r\nOnce during your turn (before your attack), you may look at your opponent’s hand. You may use the effect of a Supporter card you find there as the effect of this power. (The Supporter card remains in your opponent’s hand.) You can’t use more than 1 Sharing Poké-Power each turn. This power can’t be used if Milotic is affected by a Special Condition.\r\n\r\n[R][R][C] Flare : 60', NULL),
(30, 6, 2, 'Nidoking δ', '[C][C] Linear Attack :\r\nChoose 1 of your opponent’s Pokémon. This attack does 30 damage to that Pokémon. (Don’t apply Weakness and Resistance for Benched Pokémon.)\r\n\r\n[D][C][C] Dark Horn : 60\r\nYou may discard a Basic Pokémon or Evolution card from your hand. If you do, choose 1 of your opponent’s Benched Pokémon and do 20 damage to that Pokémon. (Don’t apply Weakness and Resistance for Benched Pokémon.)', NULL),
(30, 7, 2, 'Nidoqueen δ', 'Poké-Power : Invitation\r\nOnce during your turn (before your attack), you may search your deck for a Basic Pokémon or Evolution card, show it to your opponent, and put it into your hand. Shuffle your deck afterward. This power can’t be used if Nidoqueen is affected by a Special Condition.\r\n\r\n[C][C][C] Vengeance : 30+\r\nDoes 30 damage plus 10 more damage for each Basic Pokémon and each Evolution card in your discard pile. You can’t add more than 60 damage in this way.', NULL),
(30, 8, 2, 'Ninetales δ', 'Poké-Power : Volunteer\r\nOnce during your turn (before your attack), you may remove 4 damage counters from Ninetales and discard Ninetales from Vulpix. If you do, search your deck for Ninetales or Ninetales ex and put it onto Vulpix (this counts as evolving Vulpix). Shuffle your deck afterward.\r\n\r\n[C][C] Trick Tail : 30\r\nSearch your discard pile for an Energy card and attach it to 1 of your Pokémon.', NULL),
(30, 9, 2, 'Pinsir δ', 'Poké-Body : Armor\r\nIf your opponent has 5 of more cards in his or her hand, any damage done to Pinsir by attacks is reduced by 30 (after applying Weakness and Resistance).\r\n\r\n[C] Delta Call :\r\nSearch your deck for a Pokémon that has delta on its card, show it to your opponent, and put it into your hand. Shuffle your deck afterward.\r\n\r\n[F][C][C] Guillotine : 40', NULL),
(30, 10, 2, 'Snorlax δ', 'Poké-Body : Bedhead\r\nAs long as Snorlax remains Asleep between turns, put 2 damage counters on 1 of the Defending Pokémon.\r\n\r\nPoké-Power : Dozing\r\nOnce during your turn (before your attack), if Snorlax is your Active Pokémon, you may remove 2 damage counters from Snorlax and Snorlax is now Asleep. This power can’t be used if Snorlax is affected by a Special Condition.', NULL),
(30, 11, 2, 'Togetic δ', '[C][C] Delta Copy :\r\nChoose an attack on 1 of your opponent’s Pokémon in play that has delta on its card. Delta Copy copies that attack except for its Energy cost. (You must still do anything else required for that attack.) Togetic performs that attack.\r\n\r\n[W][C] Wave Splash : 30', NULL),
(30, 12, 2, 'Typhlosion δ', 'Poké-Power : Shady Move\r\nOnce during your turn (before your attack), if Typhlosion is your Active Pokémon, you may move 1 damage counter from either player’s Pokémon to another Pokémon (yours or your opponent’s). This power can’t be used if Typhlosion is affected by a Special Condition.\r\n\r\n[P][C][C] Burning Ball : 60\r\nIf Typhlosion has at least 2 [R] Energy attached to it, the Defending Pokémon is now Burned.', 'Shady Move'),
(30, 13, 2, 'Arbok δ', '[C] Burning Venom :\r\nThe Defending Pokémon is now Burned and Poisoned.\r\n\r\n[R][R][C] Strangle : 50+\r\nIf the Defending Pokémon has δ on its card, this attack does 50 damage plus 30 more damage.', NULL),
(30, 14, 2, 'Cloyster δ', 'Poké-Body : Solid Shell\r\nPrevent all effects of attacks, including damage, done by your opponent’s Pokémon to each of your Benched Pokémon that has δ on its card.\r\n\r\n[F] Grind : 10+\r\nDoes 10 damage plus 10 more damage for each Energy attached to Cloyster.', NULL),
(30, 15, 2, 'Dewgong  δ', 'Poké-Body : Delta Protection\r\nAny damage done to Dewgong by attacks from your opponent’s Pokémon has has  δ on its card is reduced by 40 (after applying Weakness and Resistance).\r\n\r\n[C][C] Ice Beam : 20\r\nFlip a coin. If heads, the Defending Pokémon is now Paralyzed.\r\n\r\n[C][C][C] Surge : 40+\r\nIf Dewgong has at least 2 [W] Energy attached to it, this attack does 40 damage plus 20 more damage.', NULL),
(30, 16, 2, 'Gligar δ', '[C] Sting Turn :\r\nFlip a coin. If heads, the Defending Pokémon is now Paralyzed and switch Gligar with 1 of your Benched Pokémon.\r\n\r\n[C] Tail Sting : 10+\r\nIf the Defending Pokémon is Pokémon-ex, this attack does 10 damage plus 10 more damage and the Defending Pokémon is now Poisoned.', NULL),
(30, 17, 2, 'Jynx δ', 'Poké-Body : Stages of Evolution\r\nAs long as Jynx is an Evolved Pokémon, you pay [C] less to retreat your [R] and [P] Pokémon.\r\n\r\n[R][C] Fire Punch : 30', NULL),
(30, 18, 2, 'Ledian δ', 'Poké-Power : Prowl\r\nOnce during your turn, when you play Ledian from your hand to evolve 1 of your Pokémon, you may search your deck for any 1 card and put it into your hand. Shuffle your deck afterward.\r\n\r\n[M][C] Metal Star : 30\r\nIf Ledian has a Pokémon Tool card attached to it, draw 3 cards.', NULL),
(30, 19, 2, 'Lickitung δ', '[C] Lap Up :\r\nDraw 2 cards.\r\n\r\n[P] Delta Mind :\r\nPut 1 damage counter on 1 of your opponent’s Pokémon. If that Pokémon has δ on its card, put 3 damage counters instead.', NULL),
