(63, 147, 2, 'Wailord-EX', 'Pokémon-EX rule : When a Pokémon-EX has been Knocked Out, your opponent takes 2 Prize cards.\r\n\r\nAbility : Water Veil\r\nWhenever you attach an Energy card from your hand to this Pokémon, remove all Special Conditions from it.\r\n\r\n[W][W][W][W][W] High Breaching : 120\r\nThis Pokémon is now Asleep.', NULL),
(63, 148, 2, 'Kyogre-EX', 'Pokémon-EX rule : When a Pokémon-EX has been Knocked Out, your opponent takes 2 Prize cards.\r\n\r\n[W][C] Water Pulse : 30\r\nYour opponent''s Active Pokémon is now Asleep.\r\n\r\n[W][W][C][C] Giant Whirlpool : 140\r\nReturn 2 [W] Energy attached to this Pokémon to your hand.', 'Giant Whirlpool'),
(63, 149, 2, 'Primal Kyogre-EX', 'Primal Reversion rule : When 1 of your Pokémon becomes Primal Kyogre-EX Pokémon, your turn ends.\r\n\r\nPokémon-EX rule : When a Pokémon-EX has been Knocked Out, your opponent takes 2 Prize cards.\r\n\r\nα Growth : When you attach an Energy card from your hand to this Pokémon (except with an attack, Ability, or Trainer card), you may attach 2 Energy cards.\r\n\r\n[W][W][W][C] Tidal Storm : 150 damage. Move 2 Energy from this Pokémon to 1 of your Benched Pokémon. This attack does 30 damage to each of your opponent''s Benched Pokémon-EX. (Don''t apply Weakness and Resistance for Benched Pokémon.)', 'α Growth'),
(63, 150, 2, 'Groudon-EX', 'Pokémon-EX rule : When a Pokémon-EX has been Knocked Out, your opponent takes 2 Prize cards.\r\n\r\n[F][C] Rip Claw : 30\r\nFlip a coin. If heads, discard an Energy attached to your opponent''s Active Pokémon.\r\n\r\n[F][F][F][C] Massive Rend : 130', 'Massive Rend'),
(63, 151, 2, 'Primal Groudon-EX', 'Primal Evolution rule : When 1 of your Pokémon becomes Primal Groudon-EX Pokémon, your turn ends.\r\n\r\nPokémon-EX rule : When a Pokémon-EX has been Knocked Out, your opponent takes 2 Prize cards.\r\n\r\nΩ Barrier : Whenever your opponent plays a Trainer card (excluding Pokémon Tools and Stadium cards), prevent all effects of that card done to this Pokémon.\r\n\r\n[F][F][F][C] Gaia Volcano: 100+ damage. If there is any Stadium card in play, this attack does 100 more damage. Discard that Stadium card.', 'Ω Barrier'),
(63, 152, 2, 'Sharpedo-EX', 'Pokémon-EX rule : When a Pokémon-EX has been Knocked Out, your opponent takes 2 Prize cards.\r\n\r\n[D][C] Hunt :\r\nSwitch 1 of your opponent''s Benched Pokémon with his or her Active Pokémon. This attack does 30 damage to the new Active Pokémon.\r\n\r\n[D][D][C] Jagged Fang : 100\r\nDiscard an Energy attached to this Pokémon. Then, discard an Energy attached to your opponent''s Active Pokémon.', NULL),
(63, 153, 2, 'Aggron-EX', 'Pokémon-EX rule : When a Pokémon-EX has been Knocked Out, your opponent takes 2 Prize cards.\r\n\r\n[M][C][C] Steel Headbutt : 50+\r\nFlip a coin. If heads, this attack does 30 more damage.\r\n\r\n[M][M][C][C] Raging Hammer : 60+\r\nThis attack does 10 more damage for each damage counter on this Pokémon.', NULL),
(63, 154, 2, 'M Aggron-EX', 'Mega Evolution rule : When 1 of your Pokémon becomes a Mega Evolution Pokémon, your turn ends.\r\n\r\nPokémon-EX rule : When a Pokémon-EX has been Knocked Out, your opponent takes 2 Prize cards.\r\n\r\n[M][M][C][C] Megaton Slam : 120+\r\nYou may flip a coin. If heads, this attack does 120 more damage. If tails, this attack does 20 damage to each of your Benched Pokémon. (Don''t apply Weakness and Resistance to Benched Pokémon.)', NULL),
(63, 155, 2, 'Gardevoir-EX', 'Pokémon-EX rule : When a Pokémon-EX has been Knocked Out, your opponent takes 2 Prize cards.\r\n\r\n[Y] Life Leap : 20\r\nHeal from this Pokémon the same amount of damage you did to your opponent''s Active Pokémon.\r\n\r\n[Y][Y][Y] Shining Wind : 100\r\nDuring your opponent''s next turn, this Pokémon has no Weakness.', 'Life Leap'),
(63, 156, 2, 'M Gardevoir-EX', 'Mega Evolution rule : When 1 of your Pokémon becomes a Mega Evolution Pokémon, your turn ends.\r\n\r\nPokémon-EX rule : When a Pokémon-EX has been Knocked Out, your opponent takes 2 Prize cards.\r\n\r\n[Y][C][C] Brilliant Arrow : 30×\r\nThis attack does 30 damage times the amount of [Y] Energy attached to all of your Pokémon.', 'Brilliant Arrow'),
(63, 157, 2, 'Archie''s Ace in the Hole', 'You may play only 1 Supporter card during your turn (before your attack).\r\n\r\nYou can play this card only when it is the last card in your hand.\r\n\r\nPut a [W] Pokémon from your discard pile onto your Bench. Then, draw 5 cards.', NULL),
(63, 158, 2, 'Maxie''s Hidden Ball Trick', 'You may play only 1 Supporter card during your turn (before your attack).\r\n\r\nYou can play this card only when it is the last card in your hand.\r\n\r\nPut a [F] Pokémon from your discard pile onto your Bench. Then, draw 5 cards.', NULL),
(63, 159, 2, 'Professor Birch''s Observations', 'You may play only 1 Supporter card during your turn (before your attack).\r\n\r\nShuffle your hand into your deck and flip a coin. If heads, draw 7 cards. If tails, draw 4 cards.', NULL),
(63, 160, 2, 'Teammates', 'You may play only 1 Supporter card during your turn (before your attack).\r\n\r\nYou can play this card only if 1 of your Pokémon was Knocked Out during your opponent''s last turn.\r\n\r\nSearch your deck for up to 2 cards and put them into your hand. Shuffle your deck afterward.', NULL),
(63, 161, 2, 'Dive Ball', 'Search your deck for a [W] Pokémon, reveal it, and put it into your hand. Shuffle your deck afterward.', NULL),
(63, 162, 2, 'Enhanced Hammer', 'Discard a Special Energy attached to 1 of your opponent''s Pokémon.', NULL),
(63, 163, 2, 'Switch', 'Switch one of your Benched Pokémon with your Active Pokémon.', NULL),
(63, 164, 2, 'Weakness Policy', '', NULL),
(10001, 1, 2, 'Bulbasaur', '[C] First Aid :\r\nRemove 1 damage counter from Bulbasaur.\r\n\r\n[G] Poison Seed :\r\nThe Defending Pokémon is now Poisoned.', NULL),
(10001, 2, 2, 'Caterpie', '[C] Tackle : 10\r\n\r\n[G] String Wrap : 10\r\nFlip a coin. If heads, until the end of your opponent''s next turn, the Defending Pokémon can''t retreat, and if the effect of an attack, Pokémon Power, Energy card, or Trainer card would change that player''s Active Pokémon, that part of the effect does nothing. ', NULL),
(10001, 3, 2, 'Metapod', 'Pokémon Power : Green Shield\r\nAs long as Metapod is in play, ignore Weakness when any of your Grass Pokémon are damaged. This power stops working while Metapod is Asleep, Confused, or Paralyzed.\r\n\r\n[G][G] Mysterious Powder : 20\r\nFlip a coin. If heads, the Defending Pokémon is now Confused. ', 'Green Shield'),
(10001, 4, 2, 'Weedle', '[C] Peck : 10\r\n\r\n[G] Poison Horn :\r\nThe Defending Pokémon is now Poisoned. ', NULL),
(10001, 5, 2, 'Kakuna', 'Pokémon Power : Poison Secretion\r\nIf Kakuna is damaged by an opponent''s attack (even if Kakuna is Knocked Out), the Attacking Pokémon is now Poisoned. This power stops working while Kakuna is Asleep, Confused, or Paralyzed.\r\n\r\n[C] Rollout : 10', 'Poison Secretion'),
(10001, 6, 2, 'Arbok', '[G][C] Wrap : 20\r\nFlip a coin. If heads, the Defending Pokémon is now Paralyzed. \r\n\r\n[G][G][G] Poison Sting : 30+\r\nThe Defending Pokémon is now Poisoned. If the Defending Pokémon was already Poisoned, this attack does 10 more damage. ', NULL),
(10001, 7, 2, 'Nidoran ♀', '[C] Tail Whip :\r\nFlip a coin. If heads, the Defending Pokémon can’t attack Nidoran ♀ during your opponent’s next turn. (Benching either Pokémon ends this effect.)\r\n\r\n[G] Poison Sting : 10\r\nFlip a coin. If heads, the Defending Pokémon is now Poisoned. ', NULL),
(10001, 8, 2, 'Nidorina', '[G][G] Strength in Numbers : 10+\r\nDoes 10 more damage for each of your Benched Nidoran♂, Nidoran♀, Nidorino, Nidorina, Nidoking, and Nidoqueen.\r\n\r\n[G][G][C] Fury Swipes : 30×\r\nFlip 3 coins. This attack does 30 damage times the number of heads. ', 'Strength in Numbers'),
(10001, 9, 2, 'Nidoran ♂', '[C] Focus Energy :\r\nDuring your next turn, Nidoran♂''s Horn Rush attack''s base damage is doubled.\r\n\r\n[G][C] Horn Rush : 40\r\nFlip a coin. If tails, this attack does nothing. ', NULL),
(10001, 10, 2, 'Nidorino', '[G][G] High-Speed Thrust : 60\r\nFlip a coin. If tails, this attack does nothing and this Pokémon does 20 damage to itself. ', NULL),
(10001, 11, 2, 'Zubat', '[C] Bite : 10\r\n\r\n[G][C] Suspicious Soundwave : 10\r\nFlip a coin. If heads, the Defending Pokémon is now Confused. ', NULL),
(10001, 12, 2, 'Golbat', '[G][G][C] Leech Life : 20\r\nHeal from this Pokémon the same amount of damage you did to the Defending Pokémon.\r\n\r\n[G][C][C][C] Nosedive : 60\r\nFlip a coin. If tails, this Pokémon does 40 damage to itself. ', NULL),
(10001, 13, 2, 'Paras', '[C] Scratch : 10\r\n\r\n[G] Scatter Spores : \r\nSearch your deck for a Basic Pokémon named Paras and put it onto your Bench. Shuffle your deck afterward. (You can’t use this attack if your Bench is full.)', 'Scatter Spores'),
(10001, 14, 2, 'Parasect', '[G][G] Toxic Spore : 10\r\nThe Defending Pokémon is now Poisoned.\r\n\r\n[G][G][C] Leech Life : 20\r\nHeal from this Pokémon the same amount of damage you did to the Defending Pokémon.', NULL),
(10001, 15, 2, 'Venonat', '[C] Disable :\r\nFlip a coin. If heads, choose 1 of the Defending Pokémon''s attacks. That Pokémon can''t use that attack during your opponent''s next turn.\r\n\r\n[G][G] Psybeam : 20\r\nFlip a coin. If heads, the Defending Pokémon is now Confused.', 'Disable'),
(10001, 16, 2, 'Venomoth', '[G][G] Stir Up Twister : 20\r\nYour opponent switches the Defending Pokémon with 1 of his or her Benched Pokémon. Then, switch your Active Pokémon with 1 of your Benched Pokémon. (Do the damage before switching the Pokémon.)\r\n\r\n[G][G][C] Rainbow Powder : 20\r\nFlip a coin. If heads, the Defending Pokémon is now Paralyzed. If tails, the Defending Pokémon is now Poisoned. ', 'Stir Up Twister'),
(10001, 17, 2, 'Bellsprout', '[C] Sway :\r\nFlip a coin. If heads, prevent all damage done to this Pokémon during your opponent’s next turn.\r\n\r\n[G] Stun Spore : 10\r\nFlip a coin. If heads, the Defending Pokémon is now Paralyzed. ', 'Stun Spore'),
(10001, 18, 2, 'Weepinbell', '[G] Regrowth :\r\nRemove all damage counters from this Pokémon. Discard all Evolution cards and Energy cards attached to this Pokémon. \r\n\r\n[G][G] Dissolve : 20\r\nFlip a coin. If heads, discard 1 Energy card attached to the Defending Pokémon.', 'Regrowth'),
(10001, 19, 2, 'Grimer', '[G] Sludge Liquid :\r\nIf the Defending Pokémon doesn''t already have a Sludge marker on it, put a Sludge marker on it. If a player''s Pokémon has a Sludge marker on it, he or she pays [C] more to retreat that Pokémon. (Sludge markers stay on the Pokémon as long as it’s in play.)\r\n\r\n[G] Spit Poison : 10\r\nFlip a coin. If heads, the Defending Pokémon is now Poisoned. ', 'Sludge Liquid'),
(10001, 20, 2, 'Koffing', 'Pokémon Power : Division\r\nWhenever an attack damages this Pokémon (even if this Pokémon is Knocked Out), you may search your deck for a Basic Pokémon named Koffing and put it onto your Bench. Shuffle your deck afterwards. This power can''t be used if your Bench is full or if this Pokémon is Asleep, Confused, or Paralyzed.\r\n\r\n[G][G] Strange Gas : 20\r\nFlip a coin. If heads, all Pokémon Powers of your opponent''s Pokémon stop working until the end of your opponent''s next turn. ', 'Division'),
(10001, 21, 2, 'Weezing', 'Pokémon Power : Poison Mist\r\nOnce during your turn (before your attack), you may flip a coin. If heads, until the end of your next turn, all Poisoned Pokémon take 20 damage instead of 10 damage from Poison after each player''s turn. This power can''t be used and stops working while this Pokémon is Asleep, Confused, or Paralyzed.\r\n\r\n[G][G][G] Gas Explosion : 40\r\nThis Pokémon does 30 damage to itself. If this attack Knocks Out the Defending Pokémon and your opponent chooses a new Active Pokémon, your opponent''s new Active Pokémon becomes Poisoned. ', 'Poison Mist'),
(10001, 22, 2, 'Tangela', '[G] Constrict : 10\r\nFlip a coin. If heads, until the end of your opponent''s next turn, the Defending Pokémon can’t retreat, and if the effect of an attack, Pokémon Power, Energy card, or Trainer card would change that player''s Active Pokémon, that part of the effect does nothing.\r\n\r\n[G][C] Vine Whip : 20', 'Constrict'),
(10001, 23, 2, 'Scyther', '[G][G] Slashing Strike : 40\r\nScyther can''t use this attack during your next turn. (Benching or evolving Scyther ends this effect.) ', 'Slashing Strike'),
(10001, 24, 2, 'Pinsir', '[G] Slicing Throw : 10+\r\nFlip a coin. If heads, this attack does 10 more damage.\r\n\r\n[C][C][C] Slash : 30', 'Slicing Throw'),
(10001, 25, 2, 'Charmander', '[C] Growl :\r\nDuring your opponent''s next turn, any damage done by attacks from the Defending Pokémon is reduced by 10 (before applying Weakness and Resistance).\r\n\r\n[R][R] Flame Tail : 30', NULL),
(10001, 26, 2, 'Vulpix', '[R][R] Foxfire : 10\r\nBefore doing damage, you may switch the Defending Pokémon with 1 of your opponent''s Benched Pokémon. ', 'Foxfire'),
(10001, 27, 2, 'Growlithe', '[C][C] Errand-Running :\r\nFlip a coin. If heads, search your deck for a Trainer card, reveal it, and put it into your hand. Shuffle your deck afterwards.\r\n\r\n[R][C] Ember : 30\r\nDiscard 1 Fire Energy card attached to this Pokémon in order to use this attack. ', 'Errand-Running'),
(10001, 28, 2, 'Ponyta', '[C] Smash Kick : 10\r\n\r\n[R] Live Coal : 20\r\nFlip a coin. If tails, discard 1 Energy card attached to this Pokémon. ', NULL),
(10001, 29, 2, 'Rapidash', '[R] Flame Inferno : 10+\r\nYou may discard up to 2 Fire Energy cards attached to this Pokémon. If you do, this attack does 20 more damage for each Fire Energy card you discarded.\r\n\r\n[C][C] Kick Away : 20\r\nYour opponent switches the Defending Pokémon with 1 of his or her Benched Pokémon. ', 'Flame Inferno'),
(10001, 30, 2, 'Magmar', '[R] Burning Fire : 10+\r\nWhen you use this attack, you may discard any number of Fire Energy cards attached to your Pokémon in play. This attack does 10 damage plus 10 more damage for each Fire Energy card you discarded in this way.\r\n\r\n[R][R][C] Magma Punch : 40', 'Burning Fire'),
(10001, 31, 2, 'Moltres', '[R][R] Dry Up :\r\nChoose 1 of your opponent''s Pokémon and flip a coin until you get tails. For each heads, discard 1 [W] Energy card attached to that Pokémon, if any.\r\n\r\n[R][R][R][C] Fire Wing : 50', 'Dry Up'),
(10001, 32, 2, 'Squirtle', '[W] Water Power :\r\nDuring your next turn, this Pokémon''s Pound attack''s base damage is tripled.\r\n\r\n[C] Pound : 10', NULL),
(10001, 33, 2, 'Golduck', '[P][C] Psychic : 10+\r\nDoes 10 more damage for each Energy attached to the Defending Pokémon.\r\n\r\n[W][W][C] Wave Splash : 40', NULL),
(10001, 34, 2, 'Poliwag', '[W] Bubble : 10\r\nFlip a coin. If heads, the Defending Pokémon is now Paralyzed. ', 'Bubble'),
(10001, 35, 2, 'Poliwhirl', '[W][W] Twiddle :\r\nFlip a coin. If heads, the Defending Pokémon is now Confused. If tails, the Defending Pokémon is now Asleep.\r\n\r\n[W][C][C] Body Slam : 20\r\nFlip a coin. If heads, the Defending Pokémon is now Paralyzed. ', NULL),
(10001, 36, 2, 'Poliwrath', '[W][W] Mega Punch : 30\r\n\r\n[W][W][W] Hydro Pump : 40+\r\nDoes 10 more damage for each Water Energy attached to this Pokémon but not used to pay for this attack''s Energy cost. You can''t add more than 20 damage in this way. ', NULL),
(10001, 37, 2, 'Seel', '[C] Growl :\r\nDuring your opponent''s next turn, any damage done to this Pokémon by attacks from the Defending Pokémon is reduced by 10 (before applying Weakness and Resistance).\r\n\r\n[W][W] Ice Beam : 20\r\nFlip a coin. If heads, the Defending Pokémon is now Paralyzed. ', NULL),
(10001, 38, 2, 'Dewgong', '[C][C] Rest :	\r\nRemove all damage counters from this Pokémon. This Pokémon is no longer Confused, Paralyzed, or Poisoned. This Pokémon is now Asleep.\r\n\r\n[W][W][W] Aurora Wave : 30\r\nFlip a coin. If heads, the Defending Pokémon is now Confused. ', 'Rest'),
(10001, 39, 2, 'Shellder', '[W][C] Water Spout : 20+\r\nDoes 10 more damage for each Water Energy attached to this Pokémon but not used to pay for this attack''s Energy cost. You can''t add more than 20 damage in this way. ', NULL),
(10001, 40, 2, 'Krabby', '[W] Bubble : 10\r\nFlip a coin. If heads, the Defending Pokémon is now Paralyzed.\r\n\r\n[W][C][C] Guillotine : 30', 'Bubble'),
(10001, 41, 2, 'Kingler', '[W] Salt Water :\r\nFlip a coin. If heads, search your deck for up to 3 [W] Energy cards and attach them to this Pokémon.\r\n\r\n[W][W][W][W] Double-Edged Claw : 80\r\nDuring your opponent’s next turn, all damage done to this Pokémon is doubled. ', 'Salt Water'),
(10001, 42, 2, 'Horsea', '[C] Hide :\r\nFlip a coin. If heads, prevent all effects of attacks, including damage, done to this Pokémon during your opponent''s next turn.\r\n\r\n[W] Water Gun : 10+\r\nDoes 10 more damage for each Water Energy attached to this Pokémon but not used to pay for this attack''s Energy cost. You can''t add more than 20 damage in this way. ', NULL),
(10001, 43, 2, 'Seadra', '[W][W] Water Bomb : 20\r\nDoes 10 damage for each Water Energy attached to this Pokémon but not used to pay for this attack''s Energy cost to your opponent''s Benched Pokémon in any way you like. You can''t do more than 20 damage in this way. (Don''t apply Weakness or Resistance for Benched Pokémon.)', 'Water Bomb'),
(10001, 44, 2, 'Staryu', '[W] Strange Beam : 10\r\nDuring your opponent''s next turn, your Water Pokémon that have damage counters on them have no Weakness.\r\n\r\n[W][C] Spinning Attack : 20', 'Strange Beam'),
(10001, 45, 2, 'Lapras', '[C] Sing :\r\nFlip a coin. If heads, the Defending Pokémon is now Asleep.\r\n\r\n[W][W] Surf : 30', NULL),
(10001, 46, 2, 'Omanyte', 'Pokémon Power : Prehistoric Dream\r\nOnce during your turn (before your attack), you may flip a coin. If heads, for the rest of the turn, if an attack by 1 of your Pokémon that evolves from Mysterious Fossil damages the Defending Pokémon, that attack does 10 more damage to the Defending Pokémon.\r\n\r\n[C][C] Rolling Tackle : 20', 'Prehistoric Dream'),
(10001, 47, 2, 'Omanyte', 'Pokémon Power : Fossil Guidance\r\nOnce during your turn (before your attack), you may flip a coin. If heads, put 1 Mysterious Fossil from your discard pile into your hand. This power can''t be used if Omanyte is Asleep, Confused, or Paralyzed.\r\n\r\n[W][W] Surf : 30', 'Fossil Guidance'),
(10001, 48, 2, 'Omastar', '[W] Tentacle Grip :	\r\nFlip a number of coins equal to the number of Water Energy attached to Omastar. For each heads, draw 2 cards.\r\n\r\n[W][W][W] Corrosive Acid : 40\r\nFlip a coin. If heads, the Defending Pokémon is now Paralyzed. If tails, you can''t use this attack during your next turn. ', 'Tentacle Grip'),
(10001, 49, 2, 'Articuno', 'Pokémon Power : Aurora Veil\r\nAs long as Articuno is your Active Pokémon, your Benched Pokémon do not take damage and are not affected by attacks. This power cannot be used if Articuno is affected by a Special Condition.\r\n\r\n[W][W][C][C] Ice Beam : 30\r\nFlip a coin. If heads, the Defending Pokémon is now Paralyzed.', 'Aurora Veil'),
(10001, 50, 2, 'Pikachu', '[L] ThunderShock : 10\r\nFlip a coin. If heads, the Defending Pokémon is now Paralyzed.\r\n\r\n[L][L] Agility : 20\r\nFlip a coin. If heads, during your opponent''s next turn, prevent all effects of attacks, including damage, done to Pikachu. ', NULL),
(10001, 51, 2, 'Pikachu', '[L] Recharge :\r\nSearch your deck for a Lightning Energy card and attach it to Pikachu. Shuffle you deck afterward.\r\n\r\n[L][L][L] Thunderbolt : 50\r\nDiscard all Energy cards attached to Pikachu in order to use this attack. ', 'Recharge'),
(10001, 52, 2, 'Raichu', '[L][L] Short Circuit :	\r\nChoose 1 of your opponent''s Pokémon. This attack does 10 damage to that Pokémon times the number of Water Energy cards attached to it. Don''t apply Weakness or Resistance.\r\n\r\n[L][L][C] Sparking Kick : 30\r\nFlip a coin. If heads, the Defending Pokémon is now Paralyzed. ', 'Short Circuit'),
(10001, 53, 2, 'Magnemite', 'Pokémon Power : Magnet\r\nOnce during your turn (before your attack), you may flip a coin. If heads, search your deck for a Basic Pokémon named Magnemite and put it onto your Bench. Shuffle your deck afterwards. This power can''t be used if your Bench is full or if this Pokémon is Asleep, Confused, or Paralyzed.\r\n\r\n[L] Superconductivity : 	\r\nDoes 10 damage to 1 of your opponent''s Pokémon. Don''t apply Weakness or Resistance. ', 'Magnet'),
(10001, 54, 2, 'Magneton', '[L][L][C] Microwave :	\r\nDoes 20 damage to 1 of your opponent’s Pokémon. Don’t apply Weakness or Resistance. Then, flip a coin. If heads, discard 1 Energy card attached to that Pokémon. ', NULL),
(10001, 55, 2, 'Voltorb', '[L] Thundershock : 10\r\nFlip a coin. If heads, the Defending Pokémon is now Paralyzed.\r\n\r\n[L][L] Group Spark : 20+\r\nThis attack does 10 more damage for each Voltorb in play.', 'Group Spark'),
(10001, 56, 2, 'Electabuzz', '[L] Lightning Rod :\r\nChoose 1 of your opponent''s Pokémon and put a Lightning Rod marker on it. (A Pokémon can have only 1 Lightning Rod marker on it at a time.)\r\n\r\n[L][L] Lightning Bolt : 10\r\nThis attack does 20 damage to any Pokémon with a Lightning Rod marker on it. Apply Weakness and Resistance.', 'Lightning Rod'),
(10001, 57, 2, 'Zapdos', '[L][L][L] Raging Thunder : 50\r\nFlip a coin. If tails, this attack does 30 damage to 1 of your Pokémon. (Don''t apply Weakness and Resistance.)\r\n\r\n[L][L][C][C] Thunder Crash : 50+\r\nFlip a coin. If heads, this attack does 20 more damage. If tails, this Pokémon does 20 damage to itself. ', 'Raging Thunder'),
(10001, 58, 2, 'Sandshrew', '[F] Poison Sting : 10\r\nFlip a coin. If heads, the Defending Pokémon is now Poisoned.\r\n\r\n[F] Swift : 20\r\nThis attack’s damage isn''t affected by Weakness, Resistance, Pokémon Powers, or any other effects on the Defending Pokémon. ', 'Swift'),
(10001, 59, 2, 'Sandslash', '[F] Sand Veil :\r\nFlip a coin. If heads, prevent all damage done to this Pokémon during your opponent''s next turn.\r\n\r\n[F][F][F] Rolling Needle : 40+\r\nFlip 3 coins. This attack does 10 more damage for each heads. Then, this Pokémon does 10 damage times the number of heads to itself. ', 'Rolling Needle'),
(10001, 60, 2, 'Machop', '[C] Focused One Shot :\r\nFlip a coin. If heads, during your next turn, this Pokémon''s Corkscrew Punch attack''s base damage is doubled. If tails, this Pokémon can''t use Corkscrew Punch during your next turn.\r\n\r\n[F][C] Corkscrew Punch : 30', NULL);
